Package: INLAocc
Title: Occupancy Models via Integrated Nested Laplace Approximation
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Gilles", "Colling", email = "gilles.colling051@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-3070-6066"))
Description: Fits single-species, multi-species, spatial, temporal, integrated,
    and spatially-varying coefficient occupancy models using Integrated Nested
    Laplace Approximations (INLA). Provides a fast alternative to MCMC-based
    frameworks like 'spOccupancy', with a compatible API including mixed-model
    random effects syntax, posterior predictive checks, WAIC, k-fold
    cross-validation, and design-matrix prediction. Uses an EM algorithm with
    INLA at each M-step for the two-process (occupancy/detection) likelihood.
